node.text:
Tried squatting 5 plates before this and absolutely sh*t the bed. I was not happy with the set and wasn’t walking away from the squat rack not satisfied. So after calling myself a little B word a few times I decided to do a fun little drop set seen here.
The goal was 20 reps... ended up getting 15 reps at 405lbs and just over 10 at 315lbs. Then I was able to limp away from the squat rack satisfied👌🏼
I’ll post the 5 plates set on @cbumfitness

node.text:
Did a set of 5 plates before this hoping it would feel light weight baby, but it was definitely heavy weight daddy so decided to torture myself with some high volume squats immediately after💀

🚨ALSO got something really exciting coming up, me and @melissabum are going to be having a transformation contest. With most peoples gyms opening back up it’s the perfect time to start some good habits and get back in shape or into your best shape.
You’ll be getting nutrition and training plans as well as check ins from either myself or Melissa to guide you through the process. We’re going to make it a fun sibling rivalry of team MelBum vs team Cbum with prizes for the best transformation.
With myself starting prep in a few weeks as well it’ll be like you guys are prepping with me.
I’ll have a lot more info to come at the beginning of next week so if your interested keep an eye out for the announcement👀

node.text:
The real pressure comes when you show what you’re truly capable of, because now everyone expects nothing less.
That is a privilege.
To be held at a high standard and have nothing but greatness expected of you.
Not many will understand and most won’t give a shit, but it’s something I aspire to earn every day.
#PressureIsAPrivilege #SetTheStandard
@mrolympiallc
@w_wittmannphoto

node.text:
My favorite merch launch to date, link is in my bio. Rockin the Pressure Is A Privilege fire edition T. We restocked 3 Thavage t-shirt colorways and much more.
👇🏼
Also here’s my full workout:
Smith Squats - 2 working sets. First set 8-10 reps.
Second set drop set aiming for 10-12 each time.
Walking Lunges - 2 working sets. 8-10 reps each leg, drop set to body weight second set.
Single Leg Leg Press - 2 working sets. Both Kobe sets (aim for 24 reps)
Quad Extensions - 2 working sets. Full stack to failure for me lol.
Adductors - 3 working sets, 10-12 reps.
Seated Calf raise - 4 working sets. 12-15 reps first 3 sets, then triple drop set last set.
P.S. all workouts I do any more are posted daily on my @cbumfitness app🙏🏼

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Chris Bumstead on July 19, 2021 tagging @jacked_factory, and @3rdi.imagery. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
JULY 21st OFFICIAL RESTOCK DATE.
THE DAY IS FINALLY COMING.
It’s with great excitement I get to tell you guys @jacked_factory has informed me that we have the restock confirmed for July 21, 2021 at 12pm EST.
My apologies for the delay, but we’re getting it done.
I’m hoping we have enough stock so that everyone has a chance to get it before selling out again, but... no guarantees so be on your toes this Wednesday.
 Time to go #FullThavage
Appreciate you guys🙏🏼
